Dark Sun bridge is bars 65-94 so quite long. There is also a sort of "pre bridge" transition of 7 bars where there some texture synth applied and a drum fill that signals there is a change happening before we get there.  There is a similar post bridge transition of similar length where there are some drum fills and synth shimmers signaling we are going back to the main part soon. The bridge part also moves to a higher tempo from 120bpm to 128.  (It shoudl move back to 120 at the end but does not which is sort of a mistake, but given the bridge is late in the song it just maintains the more brisk tempo to the finish.)  The bridge has some instruments drop out. There's a very different solo melody in the bridge that drives the section. It appears twice which is why the bridge is quite long. (The bridge melody is doubled by an electric guitar but that was not MIDI, but the idea is still good.) The bass is completely different during the bridge.\
\
\
Mister Mosca bridge (drum hits) occurs bars 50-56 with some instruments standing down during that and others coordinated around the drum hits, playing together. The last bar has a nice melodic descent while alternating with the root.  This style or variations thereof could be used for a short bridge that would feel dramatic.\
\
Caligari drop bridge is bars 30-38 so again fairly short. there clear drum hits at the start of every second bar (so four hits in total.) These are doubled by a synth brass track. Note that the pulsating pad bass truck is actually muted during this section. So even though it has notes, they are not played.  There is a melodic bass part that appears after the hits creating a sort of call and response (though much more complex.)  The bass is also doubling the drum and brass hits, though they are hard to hear over the drums.\
\
Note the dramatic build up bridges of Electric Buddha Band, Caligari Drop and Mister Mosca are only suitable for a true A B A form, not with a repeated B.  Let me read the rest of the plan.\
\
if in doubt, during the bridge lets have fewer instruments playing. Kosmic sometimes feels very busy with Bass, Rhythm, Lead 1 sometimes Lead 2, Texture all going on at the same time.  So always make the Bridge less complicated with fewer instruments, less clutter. This is doubly important for short "dramatic" bridges.  If two instruments play identical or almost identical parts (no competing notes) that can be a good way to simplify things.  You get more tonal richness without competing for melodic space.  Let me know if you have questions about this.\
